            <p>Dr Morais Esq.<lb/>
                Honorable friend of Humanity&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>Owing to the fact that the<lb/> bearer M<hi rend="sup">rs</hi> Lepcowker is not<lb/> able to make herself understood<lb/> in the English Language&#45;&#45;She<lb/> requested me to express her desire<lb/> in writing.<lb/></p>
            <p>When her husband died 3 years<lb/> ago she was left nearly <sic>wiht out</sic><lb/> means of <sic>suport</sic> to number<lb/> of children 2 of which she placed<lb/> in the orphan house by paying<lb/> &#36;100&#45;&#45;and <del>the</del> 2 small children she<lb/> has tried&#44; like a true mother&#44; to care<lb/> for till now&#44; but owing to her<lb/> poor condition and feeble<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>health she is hardly in the<lb/> condition of supporting herself.<lb/>  She takes sick very often and her<lb/> small children are left foodless<lb/> and in misery and avoid most<lb/> disagreeable results she is as&#45;<lb/>king your kindness to aid<lb/> her in bringing these 2 children<lb/> also into the orphan house.<lb/>  She is very poor &#38; consequently<lb/> not able to pay any money<lb/> into the orphan house for the<lb/> acceptance of the children.<lb/>  With assurance that you<lb/> will follow the dictation of your<lb/> kind <del>&#63;</del> heartedness<lb/> I remain<lb/> Yours Sincerely<lb/> Dr D. A. Rosenthal<lb/></p>  
            <p>800 Passyunk Av.<lb/></p>
            </body>
